"34" text="Passive and Automatic, for example through a group of occupants{apos} data stream (location, aggregate physilogical data, social media)" weighting="0.30000000000000004" xy="25950,24208">\n						<node color="#111111" date="2009" id="ID_1544492231" link="http://www.festo.com/cms/en_corp/9776_10386.htm#id_10386" notes="InteractiveWall – a trade fair system reacts to visitors\r\n\r\nInteractiveWall demonstrates a new form of architecture that is dynamic and interactive. It combines the advantages of the bionic Fin Ray® structure with state-of-the-art automation technology from Festo. InteractiveWall can either follow a predetermined sequence of movements or interact with people in front of it. It transforms the behaviour of trade fair visitors into motion, light and music in real time." text="InteractiveWall">\n						</node>\n						<node color="#111111" date="2005" id="ID_412415251" link="http://www.interactivearchitecture.org/reciprocal-space-ruairi-glynn.html" notes="Ruari Glynn, Reciprocal Space: double wall that reacts to presence of people entering the enclosed space" text="Reciprocal Space">\n						</node>\n						<node color="#000000" date="2013" id="99" link="http://adsdf.co.uk/digitalcapabilities.html" notes="ADSDF Architects and University of Lincoln, Digital Capabilities, Chelsea Flower show - A kinetic facade is used to reflect the emotions of groups of people, via Twitter. Twitter is mined for specific search terms, which are then reflected on the facade." text="Digial Capabilities">\n						</node>\n					</node>\n				</node>\n				<node color="#990000" id="35" text="Organisations" weighting="0.4" xy="25626,24308">\n					<node color="#111111" id="36" text="Estates - the part of an organisation that looks after facilities including buildings" weighting="0.30000000000000004" xy="25931,24356">\n					</node>\n					<node color="#111111" id="37" text="Occuping organisation - the part of an organisation that actually occupies a particular building or set o